<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-20T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-20T17:00:00-05:00" n="433" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d433">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">882.51/935: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bundy</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-20T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 20,
                                            1919, 6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Your May 12, 5 p.m.</p>
                            <p>In view of loan negotiations and affairs affecting Liberia now under
                                consideration in Paris, suggest Liberian Government defer
                                commissioning French customs receiver until definite plans for the
                                proposed rehabilitation of Liberia are concluded.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>